title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson Model 639 - All Stainless Steel 9mm - All Original!
postcontent:
For sale: Smith & Wesson Model 639 

This is a single/double action 9mm Luger pistol.  It is in all original condition, all stainless steel, and comes complete with the original textured factory walnut grips.  I do not appraise guns for a living, but I personally believe that this gun is pretty close to mint condition!  There have been no modifications to the gun whatsoever.  Everything operates just as it should, and the action functions just as you would expect.  This is the early and most preferred “round trigger guard” model. 

The gun comes complete in the original factory box and includes the instruction manual and all of the literature that was originally packed in the box from the factory.  Also included is the original and unopened cleaning and tool kit and two original Smith & Wesson-brand stainless steel eight-round magazines.  The box even has the original non-corrosive paper wrapping to protect the gun during shipment from the factory and long-term storage.

This Smith & Wesson Model 639 has a 4-inch barrel, adjustable rear sights, exposed hammer (which allows you to fire the first round in single-action mode) and de-cocker lever.  This gun is slightly smaller than a 1911, although its design evokes the traditional 1911 look.  It is still a hefty gun, however, at just over 1.7 pounds.

There are two very minor flaws that should be mentioned for fair representation: 

-The small Smith & Wesson medallion on the left grip appears to have come loose at some point.  The medallion has been securely reaffixed to the grip, but when this repair was made, the logo on the medallion was not as squarely oriented as it probably should have been.  It doesn’t stand out as an obvious flaw, but it is something you’ll notice… especially since I’ve pointed it out :-) 

-The lanyard loop at the base of the butt of the gun has some wear.  It’s still intact, strong and functional, but there is some wear evident in this area.

I recently bought this gun from a very reputable local gun store’s used gun case, and I have put about 50 rounds through it since I’ve owned it.  I was assured that the gun has been thoroughly inspected by a qualified gunsmith, and I have no reason to doubt their appraisal.  I experienced no issues with this gun at the range.  Everything worked exactly as it should, without a misfire, feed or eject issue.  The sights seem to be set a bit low, but I have not attempted to adjust them. I love the look and feel of this gun, and I know you will too!  The reason I’m selling it is that it’s about a half pound too heavy for me to carry.  I saw it for sale, loved it, and in my excitement I bought it immediately… without actually thinking through the mechanics of carrying it.  I’m not really a gun collector, so I thought I’d offer this for sale. 

I am not a gun dealer.  I’m an Ohio resident with a valid Ohio CCW permit.  I will sell this gun in a legal manner to an Ohio resident, with a proper bill-of-sale signed by me and the buyer (the buyer will be given a copy, and I will keep a copy).  Ohio CCW holders go to the front of the line, but without a CCW permit, a valid Ohio driver’s license will be required to establish Ohio residency.  Out-of-state buyers would be responsible for shipping fees to a FFL dealer in their area, as well as any fees the FFL dealer may charge.  I’m a good guy, and I will only deal with other good guys and gals.  If I ever see this gun again, I want to make damn sure I won’t be looking down its barrel.

title: For Sale:  Zeiss Fero-Z51 Night Vision, German made starlight scope
postcontent:
In perfect condition, battery closure, all knobs, etc are in perfect condition. The only flaw is one side of a sticker on it is starting to peel (who needs a sticker?) The Orion 80/I made by Zeiss/Eltro is a high-quality starlight night vision scope currently in use by the German Bundeswehr. This scope features high-tech XX1211 and XX 1340 image intensifier tubes, flash protection capabilities, reticle adjusters, focus knob, on/off button and shade control knob, reticle brightness knob and a rubber protection cover. Each scope comes with the original storage case and the following mounts: HK-made G3 claw mount with adapter plate MG3 Lafette tripod mount with adapter plate PzF 3/PzF 44 grenade launcher mount Quick-change adapter attached to the scope. This adapter can be mounted on a Picatinny rail (not included) and if it is removed it can be attached directly to a Stanag mount or to the G3 claw mount minus the adapter plate for a low-profile sighting picture. With a Stanag Scopes To Picatinny adapter like the A.R.M.S.#7 III Adaptor, this scope can be mounted on any rifle/shotgun, optionally you can spend $10 on Amazon to buy a UTG 2nd Gen STANAG To Picatinny Adaptor Mount to mount this on any firearm. This would make a DEADLY hog or yote night vision scope. I took it out to my property and had no problem identifying a human size target at 400 yards. I do not know what the maximum range would be but it is FAR better than gen 2 NVDs plus it is German made, so I am sure that it could take some serious abuse before it failed, unlike some of the new digital NV scopes. It is built for the recoil of a 7.62x51 Nato. It amplifies available light (starlight) it does not need any IR light but an IR light could be mounted on it, it is tapped for an accessory platform on top of the unit. It can also not be detected by night vision devices due to the lack of it using IR so if you are stealth hunting you can not be spotted by someone using a NVD. I hate to let it go but i need the money. When I can afford it again this is the exact model that I will be buying. Includes the original screwdriver and mounting screw pack, microfiber lens cleaning cloth.Listing as New old stock because I was told when i bought it that it was never issued, and I have never mounted it on a rifle, just tested it for function and have ran it for maybe 20-30 min checking it out. Has never been exposed to bright lights or daylight, works perfectly.

Miami Shooters Club provides such a course with its team of NRA certified instructors - who will teach students the important fundamentals of how to safely use a semi-automatic pistol and revolver. Your concealed weapons permit will allow you to concealed carry in more than 30 states.

The classes are designed for complete beginners who have never touched a gun before... but experienced shooters will learn something as well.

title: For Sale:  1940's - Savage Arms Stevens Model 311C – 16ga – Double Bbl (S x S) Shotgun
postcontent:
**02-18-2015 - Reduced! - $325 Cash**

For sale is a used, good condition, Savage Arms Stevens Model 311C double barreled (side by side) Shotgun, chambered in rarely seen 16GA. The original “painted on” wood stock has been completely sanded and refinished with a nice cherry/walnut stain and buffed oiled finish. The receiver still has the case hardening colors to it and only minor visible surface pitting in some spots on the barrels.  The barrels are uncut and measure 28” long and feature a Modified and a Full Choke (per research I’ve done on this model this was the choke configuration for all 28” barrels chambered in 12, 20, or 16 gauge).  Length of Pull(s) measure 14” and 13” respectively.

Exact age of this gun is uncertain as it doesn’t seem to have a numerical serial number, however it does have what appears to be identifying serial letters, and according to gundigest.com, “From 1940 to 1948 no serial numbers were used on doubles, only capital letters, usually in groups of three or four…”

Overall this gun is setup to be an excellent shooter, and is just waiting to be taken out with you on your next bird or upland hunt.

title: For Sale:  6x45 AR Upper
postcontent:
My son and I built this upper together as a legal deer centerfire caliber for Virginia.  He shot his second deer with it Dec 26, 2014. Unfortunately, we will be hunting next year in a county that does not allow centerfire rifles to be used for deer so I’m selling this fine upper.  
This upper is a great hunting compliment to a 5.56mm AR as it uses the same magazines.  Pull two pins, replace your 5.56 upper with this one, reuse your BCG, charging handle, magazines, and you are ready to go and legal for deer hunting!
The 6x45mm caliber is simply a 5.56mm necked-up to accommodate the 6mm bullet.  Simply run your 5.56 brass through a 6x45 die and you have all the brass you need!  
This is the most accurate AR upper I have built.  I have only loaded 80 gr. Barnes TTSX bullets and 70 gr. Nosler solid-base bullets with BLC-2 powder.  I have not loaded anything lighter or heavier.  For me, the 70 gr. bullets do best.  My best group with this barrel was .302” at 50 yards with a 3-9x scope.  
This upper has approximately 70 rounds through it and it has never been run hard.  It was built and carried as a hunting rifle, not a plinker.
